{
  "texts": [
    "If an error is made for a reliable publisher, this corresponds to a False Positive (FP) whereas an error for an unreliable publisher would correspond to a False Negative (FN).",
    "We introduce the shifting to ensure no bias corresponds with 0, whereas positive and negative bias correspond to positive and negative values, respectively.",
    "In Figure E.1 we display various such biases for each iteration of the corpus.",
    "As seen in Table E.2, performance degrades for the more extreme political biases.",
    "There is, however, a notable difference between left-biased and right-biased publishers, and especially for the reliable right-biased publishers."
  ]
}